cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CE, cs.LG 

This paper deals with the analysis of large-scale Twitter feeds and the use of machine learning techniques to predict changes in the stock market. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other possible sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
